<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4689934>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 1. — Pseudexogone backstromi Augener,1922:A, entire worm in dorsal view (c. 9 mm long); B, anterior end in dorsal view (0.05 mm wide), median and left lateral antennae missing; C, bidentate notospines in frontal and side view; D, tip of finely spinulose capillary; E, posterior end in dorsal view (redrawn and rearranged from the original illustrations by Augener 1922). Abbreviations: see p. 536." ;
